docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:7:> kernel that went from 6.6 → 6.18 → 7.0 → (and a 7.1 we're now porting)
docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:9:> a moving target** with no stable ABI, undocumented quirks, and a factory
docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:24:May** — Reinhardt r74 (6.18.26-cix-sky1-lts + 7.0.3-cix-sky1-next) and the
docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:25:first Magnetar r78 (7.0.3-next, no LTS sibling) — but those early builds did
docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:27:**no working VPU**. "Done" meant "boots and installs," not "full driver
docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:29:**iterated almost daily through May and June**: the 7.0.x edge advanced
docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:47:| (start) | **6.6.10-cix-build-generic** (vendor) | Cix factory kernel. Drivers shipped as **prebuilt `.ko` locked to one vermagic**. Audio non-functional, NPU couldn't run inference, display black-screened. Closed, unrebuildable. |
docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:48:| **May 3** | **6.18.14/.26-cix-sky1-lts** (Sky1-Linux fork) | Forced move to get **in-tree drivers** (panthor GPU, armchina-npu, amvx VPU, drm/cix). Side effect: **every vendor 6.6 `.ko` became vermagic-incompatible** — we ripped all `cix-*-driver` debs out and re-derived each subsystem on in-tree drivers. |
docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:49:| **~May 5 (r74)** | **6.18.26-lts (default) + 7.0.3-cix-sky1-next (BETA)** | **First Reinhardt.** NEXT 7.0.3 logged SCMI transition warnings on MS-R1 BIOS. *GPU not inference-validated, NPU partial, VPU not working* (see §2.1). |
docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:50:| **~May 7–8 (r78)** | **7.0.3-cix-sky1-next — NEXT-only, no LTS sibling** | **First Magnetar** (headless server SKU). Single-kernel — a known single-point-of-failure we later reversed. |
docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:51:| **May → June** | **7.0.3 → … → 7.0.12-cix-sky1-next** (edge) | The fork's "next" branch advanced through the **entire 7.0.x series, iterating almost daily**. Tracked for STR, thermal, display — but beta and shifting constantly, so it could only ever be the *edge* slot. |
docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:52:| **June (parallel)** | **7.1-rc track** | A 7.1 release-candidate cycle ran *concurrently* with 7.0.x and **also iterated**. Shipped as honest `[BETA]` because its **SCMI mailbox transport times out on MS-R1 firmware** (FAST channel 0 never returns a TX-ack IRQ; firmware wants the CIXHA001:06 doorbell channel 8). Self-rolls-back to LTS. |
docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:53:| **June 17** | **7.0.12-cix-sky1-main** (official CIX) | CIX published `cixtech/cix-linux-main` — 76 authoritative patches (STR, thermal/energy model, proper `linlondp` display, PCIe, pinctrl ACPI, RTC). Rebased via `git am --3way`. The real foundation we'd been waiting on **the entire window**. |
docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:54:| (now) | **7.1 track** | Porting v7.0 → v7.1 (first conflict at `drivers/clk/Kconfig`); SCMI-on-7.1 still open. The target is *still* moving. |
docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:58:The early-May images **installed and booted** — that's what let us call a
docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:62:| Subsystem | First ship (r74/r78, early May) | Now (7.0.12-main, June 19) |
docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:67:| GPU (Mali-G720) | ⚠️ display only — **compute/inference not validated** | ✅ Vulkan+OpenCL, llama.cpp/LiteRT/clpeak validated (Mesa 26.1.3) |
docs/HOW-DID-WE-GET-HERE.md:70:| SCMI / power | ⚠️ warnings on NEXT | ✅ on LTS/main; ❌ still times out on 7.1 |
