post-install/36-telemetry.sh:4:# Operator requirement (2026-06-01): "telnetd enabled by default with
post-install/36-telemetry.sh:15:#      over UDP/514 — so a box that wedges mid-boot still streams its
post-install/36-telemetry.sh:18:#      reboot and can be read from rescue.target afterwards.
post-install/36-telemetry.sh:20:#      UART (ttyAMA2 does not enumerate on disk-boot; see step 4 below).
post-install/36-telemetry.sh:30:LOGHOST="192.168.207.22"   # ARGOS — fleet loghost (stays up while a target wedges)
post-install/36-telemetry.sh:120:# 3. Persistent journald (survive reboot for post-mortem)
post-install/36-telemetry.sh:138:# the MS-R1 booting from disk (only the debug harness exposes it). An enabled
post-install/36-telemetry.sh:140:# (and thus graphical.target) for the full 90s device timeout on every boot.
