docs/DRIVER_FIDELITY_7012.md:1:# CIX 7.0.12 Driver Fidelity — Validated Fixes (cixmini)
docs/DRIVER_FIDELITY_7012.md:4:on our `7.0.12-cix-sky1-next` build and are re-verified on the official
docs/DRIVER_FIDELITY_7012.md:5:`7.0.12-cix-sky1-main` kernel (the A/B **edge** build); the **6.18 LTS** kernel
docs/DRIVER_FIDELITY_7012.md:6:is the shipped default. These are the changes required for full driver bring-up.
docs/DRIVER_FIDELITY_7012.md:11:- **Overlay (no-rebuild stopgap)**: `assets/kernel/modules-overlay/7.0.12-cix-sky1-next/armchina_npu.ko` (vermagic 7.0.12-cix-sky1-next, ARCH_V3 + iova=2). post-install drops to `/lib/modules/$KVER/updates/` + depmod.
docs/DRIVER_FIDELITY_7012.md:18:- **Desktop compositing — DISABLED by default (xfwm4 `use_compositing=false`)**: on the `7.0.x` kernel the zink/kopper GL compositor **cannot create an X11 swapchain** (`zink: could not create swapchain`), even with stock panvk; panvk advertises the X11 WSI surface extensions but swapchain creation fails. xfwm4 treats that GL init failure as fatal and exits → session with no window manager. `post-install/20-desktop.sh` ships a system-wide `xfwm4.xml` with compositing off; KMS/GL/Vulkan otherwise work and the GPU stays free for compute. Re-enable once zink+panvk X11 WSI is fixed upstream.
docs/DRIVER_FIDELITY_7012.md:21:- Default 32MB untuned. Use `cma=256M` boot param (VPU headroom). NPU does NOT use CMA. `cma=2G` FAILS (DMA zone is only 2GB).
docs/DRIVER_FIDELITY_7012.md:24:- `loglevel=4` suppresses boot messages. Set `loglevel=7` in boot entry for visible boot kernel messages.
docs/DRIVER_FIDELITY_7012.md:29:  devices (`aplay -l` / `arecord -l`). Verified on `.66` (`7.0.12-cix-sky1-main`).
