codex
I found the install flow: `run-all.sh` makes `70-bootloader.sh` the final ESP writer via an EXIT trap, after numbered hooks such as `72-rescue-partition.sh`. So the generated rEFInd options in 70 are the authoritative boot behavior for a fresh install.
