   238	#
   239	# r130 SAFETY CHANGE: prior releases hard-coded /dev/nvme0n1 and unconditionally
   240	# wiped it (wipefs + sgdisk --zap-all + dd) with NO prompt. A tester (MrSBC/COS)
   241	# flagged this as dangerous, and the MS-R1 itself has more than one NVMe slot,
   242	# so a fixed target is unsafe. We now:
   243	#   - enumerate disks (NON-destructive) in early_command for operator visibility
