   158	  the base set (the desktop dead‑locks without it) and to make the real
   159	  debootstrap run in `--mode thin` with an **embedded offline mirror**.
   160	- **Post‑install hook pipeline** (`run-all.sh`) with required (fatal) Phase‑1
   161	  hooks and best‑effort Phase‑2 hooks — networking is now a fatal hook so a
   162	  box never boots half‑connected.
   163	- **systemd‑boot menu** generated with three entries (stable / edge / rescue),
   164	  **boot counting + 3‑try rollback** on edge, and a clean rescue target that
   165	  blacklists NPU/GPU/VPU/display for recovery.
   166	- **Kernel manifest + integrity** (`kernel-manifest.py`) so the staged
   167	  Image/modules/config can't silently drift from what was validated.
   168	- **Diagnostic account that self‑destructs on first successful boot** — present
   169	  for installer‑time rescue/telemetry, gone the moment the system boots
   170	  cleanly, so no known credentials persist on a running appliance.
   171	- A recurring failure mode — copying multi‑GB ISOs to macOS — was worked around
   172	  with `dd` over SSH after `scp` repeatedly stalled past 2 GB.
